## How to run "nvm" in "oh my zsh"?

use homebrew to install nvm

```sh
brew install nvm
```

edit your system configuration

```sh
    vim ~/.zshrc     # or  vim ~/.bashrc
    export NVM_DIR=~/.nvm
```

esc > :wq
save file

reload the configuration

```sh
source $(brew --prefix nvm)/nvm.sh
```

view nvm version

```sh
$ nvm --version
# 0.36.0
```
